# Root-level ad-hoc reproducer programs (e.g. test_dir_symlink.rs, test_xss.rs
# created to verify behavior outside the test harness). Real tests live under
# tests/ or in #[cfg(test)] modules; this glob applies only to the repo root.
/test_*.rs

# NTM per-repo state (rate-limit tracking, session metadata) — regenerated on demand
.ntm/
.claude/settings.local.json

# Golden-file actual-dump outputs — written by tests/golden_robot_json.rs and
# tests/pages_export_golden.rs when a golden diverges from expected, strictly
# for local diffing ahead of UPDATE_GOLDENS=1 regeneration. Never committed.
tests/golden/**/*.actual

# cargo-fuzz duplicate corpus tree, created when cargo-fuzz is invoked from
# inside the fuzz/ subcrate (default destination is `./fuzz/corpus/<target>/`,
# which from within fuzz/ resolves to `fuzz/fuzz/corpus/<target>/`). The real
# tracked corpus lives at fuzz/corpus/<target>/; this nested tree is a
# regeneratable mirror of the same seed files.
fuzz/fuzz/

# Beads compliance audit dir (managed by /beads-compliance-and-completion-verification skill)
/beads_compliance_audit/
